Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle at neck join, downcurving. Triangular stamp. Clay near fine beige-buff; some mica; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 110, 33).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1615)
